In this statement, the President sends his best wishes to Muslim communities around the world as Ramadan begins. He acknowledges that Ramadan is a festive time for Muslims and highlights the traditions of gathering for iftar and prayers, as well as the bazaars that light up cities. The President also recognizes that Ramadan is a time of deep reflection and sacrifice for Muslims, emphasizing the importance of fasting to increase spirituality and reach out to those less fortunate. He mentions the crisis in Somalia and the Horn of Africa, urging nations to come together and offer support and assistance to relief efforts. The President concludes by wishing Muslims a blessed month and expressing his anticipation for hosting an iftar dinner at the White House.